# HERMES code ownership
#
# The LAST matching pattern wins; patterns are in include-order of priority.
# Every PR requires at least one review from a listed owner; main-branch PRs
# require an additional reviewer from @Rushikesh-Palande/hermes-maintainers.
#
# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default: any change needs a maintainer review.
*                               @Rushikesh-Palande

# Docs & contracts — require an extra set of eyes since they drive behaviour.
/docs/contracts/                @Rushikesh-Palande
/docs/design/                   @Rushikesh-Palande

# Database migrations — never merge without a DBA-level review.
/migrations/                    @Rushikesh-Palande

# Detection algorithms — golden-traffic parity is load-bearing.
/services/hermes/detect/        @Rushikesh-Palande
/services/hermes/events/        @Rushikesh-Palande

# Security-sensitive code.
/services/hermes/auth/          @Rushikesh-Palande
/SECURITY.md                    @Rushikesh-Palande

# CI & packaging — break these and every build breaks.
/.github/                       @Rushikesh-Palande
/packaging/                     @Rushikesh-Palande
/docker-compose.dev.yml         @Rushikesh-Palande
/pyproject.toml                 @Rushikesh-Palande
